    public class Municipality

      • adminLevels

        protected java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> adminLevels
        Define, which boundary administrative polygons in OSM should be used to make evaluations.
        List of OSM key admin_level values.
        If List is empty, all available boundary polygons on each admin level will be used.
        This list is useful, when boundary polygons in a admin level is only partly used or in two different levels are the same boundary polygons.

      • subareasidentifyable

        protected boolean subareasidentifyable
        Depending on the official housenumber list for a municipality, this is set to true, if the list contains a sub area id field.
        In this case, the evaluation is more precise, as it nows, in which sub area a missing housenumber must be.
        If set, adminLevels must be set to two values. One value is municipality level (mostly level 8), and the second value is sub area level, which corresponds to sub area field of housenumber list
        See Also:
        adminLevels

      • languagecode

        protected java.lang.String languagecode
        Optionally field in cases, where street names in official housenumber list differs from mainly used language in OSM key name.
        Example: in Belgium, two languages are mainly used. With this field, you define a two letter ISO language code (for example NL and then OSM key name:NL will be used, near main OSM key name, to find named streets

      • search

        public static int search(java.lang.String municipalityCountry,
                         java.lang.String municipalityName,
                         java.lang.String officialRef,
                         java.lang.String adminHierachyTextform)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        search for one or many municipalities in DB and returns the number of found municipalities.
        The result will be stored internally and can get one municipality per time via calls to next()
        Parameters:
        country - In which Country the municipalities will be searched. Wildcard * allowed
        municipalityName - Name of municipality. Wildcard * allowed, to get more than one or even all municipality in country
        officialRef - Official reference of the municipality. Examine OSM key for official ref in country via Country.getOfficialReferenceOsmKey()
        adminHierachyTextform - filter municipalities via admin hierarchy in textform. For example "Bundesrepublik Deutschland,Bayern". Wildcard * allowed
        Returns:
        number of found municipalities in DB
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
